# Pull requests — story workflow

## When this applies

Use when the user is **opening**, **editing**, or **reviewing** a GitHub PR tied to `docs/agile/epics/**/stories/US-*/STORY.md`.

## Title

```text
[US-{DOMAIN}-{NNN}] {short title from story}
```

Example: `[US-DESIGN-002] Editor + AI chat design tokens & dark-mode polish`

## Body

1. Prefer **`PR_BODY.md`** in the same story folder (e.g. `docs/agile/epics/EPIC-DESIGN-01/stories/US-DESIGN-002/PR_BODY.md`) and pass it to GitHub:

   ```bash
   gh pr create --base main --title "..." --body-file docs/agile/epics/EPIC-DESIGN-01/stories/US-DESIGN-002/PR_BODY.md
   ```

2. Otherwise paste sections from **STORY.md**: user story, AC checklist, tests, out of scope.

3. Align with templates in `.github/pull_request_template.md` and `.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/story.md`.

## Commands

- Full step-by-step: `docs/agile/guides/STORY_PR_WORKFLOW.md`
- `npm run pr:open:us-design-002` — opens US-DESIGN-002 PR body file (after push)
- PowerShell: `scripts/open-story-pr.ps1`

## Rules

- One **story** per branch / per PR when possible (`docs/agile/GIT_STRATEGY.md`).
- Do not put `Made-with: Cursor` or similar trailers in commits (`.cursor/rules/commit-messages.mdc`).
- After merge: update `STORY.md` PR #, `EPIC.md`, `TEAM_STATUS.md` per `docs/agile/HOW_TO_USE.md` §7.
